<br>
He will be a male Shadow Knight, very loyal to Thule and his beliefs, but not necessarily always a run in swinging, confrontational type. He's a cool, calculating, erudite Erudite. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Khatib is the name I've chosen, as it strikes me as sounding like a name for an Erudite. It is borrowed from middle eastern muslim society. Any feedback on the name, does it fit to y'all?<br>
<br>
Resource material, anyone? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uderganpuppyeater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dergan Puppyeater</A> at: 9/26/02 11:29:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/26/02 4:17:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2763.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm.</span><hr size=1> 1.  Make a (good) Erudite (with a diety, preferrably the rare Quellious) on another server and run around in Erudin talking to the various NPCs there.  This will allow you to flesh out what you're up against, if you decide to have family/plots dealing with that side.<br>
<br>
ESPECIALLY the magician's guild and the jailer staff, regarding executions...knowing what you're up against and not caring may add some dimension.<br>
<br>
Then when you first make Khatib, explore Paineel a bit.  Get a feel for how NPCs treat you.  (PCs...well, people in Paineel all tend to be people who kill guards, and are generally people who can't be bothered to go to a real dungeon.)<br>
<br>
2.  Snooty.  Arrogant.  Has the skills to back up his cool and calculating nature.  Erudites aren't just Snooty.  They're CONFIDENT and Snooty.  If Khatib isn't, then he should probably the last to speak sort of person (opens his mouth and shuts people up with the right answer, etc.)<br>
<br>
3.  Snazzy Dresser?  Vain?<br>
<br>
4.  Weapon choice.  Whatever's around, or a preference?  Spears?  Axes?  Daggers?  Stilettos?  Clubs?  Hammers?  Big Hammers?  Maces?  Staves?  Two-handed swords?  One-handed swords?<br>
<br>
Most general thought on Shadowknights is &quot;train all skills&quot; (except maybe 2HB, although there are a few good hammers out there)<br>
<br>
I'd see him using mainly staves and other &quot;non-lethal&quot; *snickers* weapons.<br>
<br>
5.  Erudites are far from the direct approach, but Shadowknights get away with it.  Focus on INT mainly, if you want to be more of a technical Shadowknight with a sort of fighting style.<br>
<br>
Although starting stats for a Erudite Shadowknight should *probably* be:<br>
<br>
STR/STA/DEX/AGI--INT/WIS/CHA<br>
75/75/75/75--122/83/75.<br>
<br>
Any stat under 75 has penalties associated with it...ESPECIALLY DEX/AGI considering you are a melee.<br>
<br>
6.  You may want to grab a shade silk robe. They look GREAT on Erudites (with hair, *do* use hair on the new models) and are good for lounging around in.  I lost mine...to the New UI 'loot too fast' bug; I do miss it; have to bother to make another...<br>
<br>
7.  Paineel doesn't have many allies--it is a very isolated city.  Be careful about who you call friend.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Antoin Nolouj
