<br>
Like, I'm trying to figure out Khatib's life thus far... did he grow up in a barracks, or in the home of his parents? I think I want him to be somewhat shunned by Heretic society, even though he's loyal to Thule and a sworn enemy of &quot;good&quot; Erudites.<br>
<br>
Where can I get one of those robes? Are they decent AC for a newbie, and cheap? I'm thinking I will train all weapon styles except for two handed blunt, just because I like versatility... I am going to carry this into character for the same reason; he likes versatility, but he favors a one handed blade and the use of a shield. He prefers a clean death to the brutal type from a mace and doesn't use those in battle unless he needs a prisoner, and he uses torture only when necessary... not because of any sense of mercy or guilt, but because it is a tool which can cause fear and get information, but is inefficient other than that... and efficiency is what rules his life.<br>
<br>
Are the Heretics a type of brotherhood? Like, if I meet one in a distant place, would we be all close? How large is the community of Paineel? Everyone knows everyone?<br>
<br>
Back to the outcast thing... (haha, I just realized he'd be an outcast among outcasts... yikes), I say that I may take him that way because of the way I think he would do things, and the way I think most Heretics would do things... would that set him apart, make him sort of outcast? Like, if he sometimes travels through good lands and puts on the guise of a regular Erudite who knows some magic and is skilled with a sword, like a traveller or something? Or is this an accepted thing to do, to walk unseen among the enemy?<br>
<br>
As for pre-set racial prejudices, I know I hate Erudites who aren't Heretics... what about everyone else? I mean, I know I have a general disdain for most other races... what about the high elves? Do I respect them or hate them all the more for their almost-peer level? And the Dark Elves... We have a loose alliance, right? Can I walk freely in most cities, other than Qeynos?<br>
<br>
Do Heretics, or at least the ShadowKnights, follow a code of honor? If not, would it be weird for me to have my own code of honor? How do most Erudites feel about the Iksar?<br>
<br>
Thank you very much, if you happened to wade through all this. I am very thankful to those of you who are experienced enough to share the precedences which have evolved from this interesting Verant made society... a shame I can't just do a search at google and get a ton of material <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
