<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Where can I get one of those robes? Are they decent AC for a newbie, and cheap?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Tailored, ~51 trivial.  Two Shade Silk Swatches, Tunic Pattern.<br>
<br>
AC6 AGI1 all/all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Are the Heretics a type of brotherhood? Like, if I meet one in a distant place, would we be all close? How large is the community of Paineel? Everyone knows everyone?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not everyone knows everyone, but there's this general level of respect, even for Good / Neutral Erudites.<br>
<br>
As for Heretics...never seen Heretics fight each other.  Sparring is okay.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Or is this an accepted thing to do, to walk unseen among the enemy?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Antoin does it all the time.  I often disguised myself as an enchanter when I went to see neutrals I was trying to corrupt.<br>
<br>
Order / Evil if you take the D&amp;D equivalent Lawful Evil, you get someone who works within the system but bends the rules to their end.  Corruptor-types often are &quot;Order Evil&quot; characters.  (Since the Alignment System's gone...but for the record ERU/SHD could ONLY be Order / Evil.  Alignment Change 8 if I recall.)  Officially Paineel has few enemies, but Erudites are always big on spying.  Loyalists are big on spying and diplomacy; Heretics are big on spying and sabotage/subterfuge. (There's a Heretic quest to poison the water of the Warrens.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As for pre-set racial prejudices, I know I hate Erudites who aren't Heretics... what about everyone else? I mean, I know I have a general disdain for most other races... what about the high elves? Do I respect them or hate them all the more for their almost-peer level? And the Dark Elves... We have a loose alliance, right? Can I walk freely in most cities, other than Qeynos?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually not really.<br>
<br>
Qeynos -- fixable faction, initally threatening (SK only; CLR dubious)<br>
Halas -- KOS.<br>
Surefall Glade -- KOS.<br>
Erudin -- walkable for the most part until you start questing.<br>
Rivervale -- KOS.<br>
Freeport -- walkable.<br>
Karanas -- threatening, fixable, but who cares?<br>
High Keep -- threatening, fixable.<br>
Oggok -- KOS.<br>
Grobb -- KOS.<br>
Neriak -- walkable, except the ghouls.  (ITU is needed to get to the SK guild.)<br>
Kaladim -- KOS.<br>
Ak`Anon -- threatening?<br>
Kelethin / Felwithe -- Dubious.  Yes, Dubious.<br>
Shar Vahl -- indifferent<br>
Cabilis -- KOS.<br>
FV outpost -- KOS<br>
Overthere -- apprehensive.<br>
Thurgadin -- apprehensive.<br>
Kael -- threatening.<br>
CoV -- KOS.<br>
<br>
Your options are pretty limited, but most major cities that are worth anything are fixable.  Neriak, Freeport, Qeynos are going to be your main goals and are pretty easy to get in.  High Keep is a necessity for travel.<br>
<br>
Shar Vahl is a nice touch but no guildmaster.<br>
<br>
Cabilis and Ak`Anon are nice touches...but not really required until you trash OT faction or spend too much time in Faydwer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Do Heretics, or at least the ShadowKnights, follow a code of honor? If not, would it be weird for me to have my own code of honor? How do most Erudites feel about the Iksar?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Code of Honors are common.<br>
<br>
Erudites and Iksar sorta...well it's a mixed bag.  Half and half hate and tolerate, I'd say.  Bit of jealousy over being the &quot;true children of Thule.&quot; etc.<br>
<br>
Although Iksar Shamen CAN use the Cleric Medallions from Paineel;<br>
Cabilis hates all Hertics.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Antoin Nolouj
